PostgreSQL provides various operators and functions for querying
(Extract JSON element by key/index): Extracts a JSON object or array element.
SELECT details->'brand' FROM products WHERE name = 'Laptop';
(Extract JSON element as text): Extracts a JSON object or array element as text.
SELECT details->>'model' FROM products WHERE name = 'Laptop';
(Extract JSON sub-object at specified path): Extracts a nested JSON sub-object.
SELECT details#>'{specs,cpu}' FROM products WHERE name = 'Laptop';
(Extract JSON sub-object as text): Extracts a nested JSON sub-object as text.
SELECT details#>>'{specs,ram}' FROM products WHERE name = 'Laptop';
(Contains operator): Checks if a JSON document contains another JSON document.
(Key exists operator): Checks if a top-level key exists.
For optimized query performance, especially with large datasets,
(Generalized Inverted Index) indexes are highly recommended on
CREATE INDEX idx_products_details_gin ON products USING GIN (details);
